	<div id="p126288" class="post bg1">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p126288">Re: DIY Yogurt</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="https://taiwanease.com/en/forums/post126288.html?sid=cb0962ece7560f5c49d802b3bbe6ae1d#p126288"><img src="https://taiwanease.com/en/forums/styles/art_elegance_taiwanease/imageset/icon_topic_latest.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="https://taiwanease.com/en/forums/member/cranky%20laowai/?sid=cb0962ece7560f5c49d802b3bbe6ae1d" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">cranky laowai</a></strong> &raquo; Tue May 31, 2016 17:12 </p>

			

			<div class="content">I usually initially heat the milk more, to around 60 degrees C (140 F). Some people like to heat it even more, up to around 80 C. This is supposed to make the yogurt thicker, though I haven't experimented with this myself. <br /><br />I have a <a href="http://www.pcstore.com.tw/eoutlet/M00965647.htm" onclick="window.open(this.href);return false;" class="postlink">Sampo yogurt maker</a>, which basically just keeps the yogurt a little warm. I think it came free with a credit card application or something like that. (If you have a gas oven with a pilot light, that would be warm enough by itself -- but in Taiwan those aren't really available.) It's nice to have the yogurt maker, especially in the winter; but it's a little difficult to come by containers that fit inside it. (I use a tall glass jar that holds about 750 ml of milk.)<br /><br />You can also buy yogurt starter at many stores. Keep it in the freezer, so it's handy if you don't have fresh yogurt around that you can use. It's around NT$420 for a box of 20 packets. I use just half a packet each time rather than a whole one. Works fine for me. <br /><br />I tend to make yogurt at night and take it out of the warmer in the morning. In the winter, starting earlier in the evening would be a good idea if you want to finish at about the same time.  <img src="https://taiwanease.com/en/forums/images/smilies/twocents.gif" alt=":twocents:" title="IMHO" /></div>

			<div id="sig126288" class="signature"><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.pinyin.info/news/">http://www.pinyin.info/news/</a><!-- m --></div>
                        <hr />
                        
                        <div class="content">
                                
