			<h3 ><a href="#p126332">Re: DIY Yogurt</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="https://taiwanease.com/en/forums/post126332.html?sid=cb0962ece7560f5c49d802b3bbe6ae1d#p126332"><img src="https://taiwanease.com/en/forums/styles/art_elegance_taiwanease/imageset/icon_topic_latest.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="https://taiwanease.com/en/forums/member/SlowRain/?sid=cb0962ece7560f5c49d802b3bbe6ae1d">SlowRain</a></strong> &raquo; Wed Jun 01, 2016 22:25 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Thanks for the replies.<br /><br />My goal is a slightly thick texture, maybe like a pudding or something similar to that.  I'm not going to be drinking it or cooking with it.  About how many hours should I let it sit?  Does the sitting affect the texture or the taste, or both?  Am I correct in assuming my initial choice for what I use as a starter will have the biggest impact on taste?<br /><br />What about flavoring?  What do you do, even if it may seem a little strange?</div>

			

