			<h3 ><a href="#p126634">Re: DIY Yogurt</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="https://taiwanease.com/en/forums/post126634.html?sid=cb0962ece7560f5c49d802b3bbe6ae1d#p126634"><img src="https://taiwanease.com/en/forums/styles/art_elegance_taiwanease/imageset/icon_topic_latest.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="https://taiwanease.com/en/forums/member/SlowRain/?sid=cb0962ece7560f5c49d802b3bbe6ae1d">SlowRain</a></strong> &raquo; Wed Jun 08, 2016 12:31 </p>

			

			<div class="content">A couple more quick questions:<br /><br />Can I strain the yogurt through a sterilized tea strainer, or is the tofu cloth better? <br /><br />I may consider a cup of that AB as my starter, but are there any stores that have a variety of cultures to choose from and are specifically targeting people making yogurt at home? <br /><br />What about the simple counter-top method which, as I understand it, doesn't require any heating, and where time, more so than temperature, is the important factor?</div>

			

		</div>

		


